description.narrative:
SPPD will work closely with Directorates across the Secretariat to drive and demonstrate improved organisational performance and results. In doing so it will enhance value for money for its members and stakeholders and position the organisation as a competitive recipient for funding, as well as an expert in its strategic focus areas that delivers impact for its members and their public. It will do this by:
Preparing and stewarding the implementation of the Secretariat’s strategies including the Strategic Plan and Delivery Plan Ensuring coordination and coherence across programmes Spearheading the institutionalisation of results based management including through building staff capacity and providing guidances and tools Supporting managers to make evidence-based and data driven performance decisions including though encouraging he generation and use of performance information Monitoring, reporting and evaluating programme quality and performance Conducting quality assurance of existing processes and practices, flagging problems and driving improvements Ensuring that learning is actively sought out and shared across projects, programmes and the entire portfolio. Engaging with stakeholders towards increasing the organisation’s reach, influence and funding base Acting as the Secretariat to the Commonwealth Secretariat’s governing bodies
